        public boolean hasFullValuePrecision​(IndexQuery... predicates)
        Specified by:
        hasFullValuePrecision in interface IndexReader
        Specified by:
        hasFullValuePrecision in class NativeIndexReader<GenericKey,​NativeIndexValue>
        Parameters:
        predicates - query to determine whether index has full value precision for.
        Returns:
        whether or not this reader will only return 100% matching results from IndexReader.query(QueryContext, IndexProgressor.EntityValueClient, IndexQueryConstraints, IndexQuery...). If false is returned this means that the caller of IndexReader.query(QueryContext, IndexProgressor.EntityValueClient, IndexQueryConstraints, IndexQuery...) will have to do additional filtering, double-checking of actual property values, externally.

      • initializeRangeForGeometrySubQuery

        private boolean initializeRangeForGeometrySubQuery​(GenericKey treeKeyFrom,
                                                   GenericKey treeKeyTo,
                                                   IndexQuery[] query,
                                                   CoordinateReferenceSystem crs,
                                                   SpaceFillingCurve.LongRange range)
        Initializes treeKeyFrom and treeKeyTo from the query. Geometry range queries makes an otherwise straight-forward key construction complex in that a geometry range internally is performed by executing multiple sub-range queries to the index. Each of those sub-range queries still needs to construct the full composite key - in the case of a composite index. Therefore this method can be called either with null or non-null crs and range and constructing a key when coming across a IndexQuery.GeometryRangePredicate will use the provided crs/range instead of the predicate, where the specific range is one out of many sub-ranges calculated from the IndexQuery.GeometryRangePredicate by the caller.
        Parameters:
        treeKeyFrom - the "from" key to construct from the query.
        treeKeyTo - the "to" key to construct from the query.
        query - the query to construct keys from to later send to GBPTree when reading.
        crs - CoordinateReferenceSystem for the specific range, if range is specified too.
        range - sub-range of a larger IndexQuery.GeometryRangePredicate to use instead of IndexQuery.GeometryRangePredicate in the query.
        Returns:
        true if filtering is needed for the results from the reader, otherwise false.
